    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a heightened U.S. military posture across multiple theaters, with particular emphasis on the Western Pacific and Southern Command regions. The tracking data indicates sustained intra-theater and strategic airlift operations, primarily conducted by C-130 and C-17 variants, supporting ongoing deployments and exercises. The USS George Washington (CVN-73) is transiting from Yokosuka for spring patrol in the Philippine Sea, while the CNS Liaoning (16) operates nearby, demonstrating a clear naval competition in the Western Pacific. The Southern Command area remains active, with the USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7) ARG transiting home after a 10-month deployment, reflecting sustained U.S. presence in the region. Maritime patrol and ISR aircraft (MH-60S/Seahawk, EC45, BE20) are heavily concentrated in the Gulf of Mexico and southeastern U.S., indicating increased focus on counter-narcotics and maritime domain awareness. Training operations, including F-5 aggressor flights and V-22 Osprey deployments, further underscore ongoing readiness and exercise activities. The data suggests a U.S. military posture geared toward maintaining global readiness, with particular attention to countering regional challenges in the Pacific and Southern Command theaters while supporting domestic and regional security operations.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
